  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2004-10-08",
    "date": "2004-11-18T16:43:17Z",
    "text": "Corporate Advance Disclosure Act of 2004 - Amends the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 to require that: (1) an issuer provide to the Securities and Exchange Commission 60 days notice in advance of any action that creates, substantially increases, or funds a non-qualified pension plan for which any director or executive officer of the issuer is the beneficiary; and (2) the notice separately state each creation, increase, or funding with respect to each such director or officer."
  },
